07/07/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Norwegian Defence Minister Kristin Krohn Devold arrives Monday (7 July) for a four-day visit at the invitation of her Romanian counterpart, Ioan Mircea Pascu. Talks will focus on issues related to Romania's admission to NATO and the process of transforming and enlarging the Alliance in the new global security context. Devold will also visit the port of Constanta, SEEBRIG headquarters and the Naval Forces Academy. (Rompres, ACT Media - 07/07/03)
